### Do you want to request a feature or report a bug?

bug

### What is the current behavior?

When trying to update a useState hook value by calling updater function (setState in this example) more than once and in sequence in an event handler, the last one overrides previous updates.

Example:
```
import React, { useState } from "react";
import ReactDOM from "react-dom";

const SomeComponent = () => {
  const [state, setState] = useState({
    value1: 0,
    value2: 0,
  });

  function onClick(event){
    setState({
        ...state,
        value1: 1,          
    });
    setState({
        ...state,
        value2: 2,         
    });
  }

  return (
    <div>      
      <button onClick={onClick}>Click Me</button>
      <h2>value1: {state.value1}</h2>
      <h2>value2: {state.value2}</h2>
    </div>
  );
};

ReactDOM.render(
    <SomeComponent />, 
document.getElementById("root"));

```
### [Code Sandbox](https://codesandbox.io/s/create-react-app-rx30c)

### What is the expected behavior?
Updating both value1 and value2 in state

### Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?
(don't seem to be version or OS specific)
**react:** 16.8.6
**browser:** chrome 76.0.3809.87
**OS:** Windows 10
